(18, 'Ultimo Suspension Lights', 'Ferdinand Verbeek', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Strength, technique and beauty unite in Ferdinand Verbeek\'s ULTIMO® suspension light. When first introduced, it was among the most slender in its class, measuring just 0.9\" wide and .06\" in height, clearly trumpeting Ferrolight\'s \"less is more\" principle and dedication to creating uncommonly linear LED light sources. Each light can be specified in either a 5.2\" or 6.6\" length in natural aluminum or anodized black. Additional sizes are available upon request. Please contact us directly at 302-295-3688 to discuss your specific project requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: H 0.6\"X W 5.2\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: H 0.6\" X W 6.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Natural Aluminum or Black Anodized Frame, 8 or 10 Sequential LED Modules of 2.5 Watts Depending on Length, Dimmer Not Included</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Dutch designer Ferdinand Verbeek founded Ferrolight in 1999 with a clear mission to create light objects of uncommon structural beauty and technical sophistication. All fixtures and lighting innovations are designed by Verbeek and hand-crafted in the Ferrolight studio in Hendrik-Ido-Ambacht, Netherlands. The designs are developed using light that shares the same natural warmth as sunlight. With an energy label of A + and A ++, each light is a technical masterpiece of the highest order. Every fitting is made from genuine materials such as anodized aluminum,&nbsp; stainless steel and wood. V4 Design Specialists is pleased to be among the select dealers promoting Ferrolight lighting products in North America.</p>\r\n', '2515', '3090', 'en', 18),
(19, 'Arcturus Suspension Lights', 'Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Graypants Massive Arcturus Scraplight captivates a space with its large diameter and warm lighting effect. Handmade in Holland, each layer of recyclable cardboard creates captivating rings of light and shadow, producing an ambient swirling effect when viewing from afar. The shade is held together with a steel frame and holds a sandblasted glass diffuser on the inside to soften the downlight below.&nbsp;Tough and elegant, each shade is precision cut with a laser and assembled by hand using a nontoxic adhesive. The Arcturus is treated with an environmentally friendly, no-burn fire retardant and is designed to perform flawlessly in both large-scale commercial applications and residential projects. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: 64\" X 64\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Handmade Shade, Natural Black Cord, Round Powder Coated Black Ceiling Canopy, Bulbs 8 - 60 Watt, 120V, Medium Base E 26 (not included)</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Architects Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker introduced their flagship line of pendant lights made entirely of repurposed corrugated cardboard in 2007. Their Scraplights quickly became a prime example of the principles that Graypants embodies to this day – responsible design, responsible materials, and responsible production. In 2012, their Amsterdam studio was founded to become a hub for local European production and distribution to over forty countries and has partnered with social works programs to provide craft-based work where needed the most. Today, Graypants continues to expand its custom portfolio, from architectural installations to public artworks, and has numerous product lines sold throughout the world. The range of their work is comprehensive, covering residential and commercial lighting, furniture, packaging designs, and architecture.</p>\r\n', '11385', '12075', 'en', 19),
(20, 'Bell Suspension Lights', 'Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Handmade with layers of corrugated cardboard, the Graypants Bell Suspension light takes recycling to new design heights, transforming the material with warm, ambient light. It\'s intricate layers create a relaxed mood&nbsp; that manages to be both modern and rustic at the same time. Graypants maintains high standards of&nbsp; sustainable production, using only FSC-certified paper and environmentally-friendly treatments for the cardboard.&nbsp;Tough and elegant, each shade is precision cut with a laser and assembled by hand using a nontoxic adhesive.&nbsp; The entire Scraplight series is designed to perform flawlessly in both commercial applications and residential projects</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: Bell 10, H 11\" X W 10.5\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements Bell 16, H 15\" X W 15,5\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials:&nbsp;Materials:&nbsp;Handmade Shade, Natural, Cord and Powder Coated Canopy in Black,&nbsp;Blonde and White, Cord and Powder Coated Canopy in White,&nbsp;Bulbs: E26, 60W 120V Medium Base (Not Included)</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Architects Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker introduced their flagship line of pendant lights made entirely of repurposed corrugated cardboard in 2007. Their Scraplights quickly became a prime example of the principles that Graypants embodies to this day – responsible design, responsible materials, and responsible production. In 2012, their Amsterdam studio was founded to become a hub for local European production and distribution to over forty countries and has partnered with social works programs to provide craft-based work where needed the most. Today, Graypants continues to expand its custom portfolio, from architectural installations to public artworks, and has numerous product lines sold throughout the world. The range of their work is comprehensive, covering residential and commercial lighting, furniture, packaging designs, and architecture.</p>\r\n', '465', '745', 'en', 20),
(21, 'Disc Suspension Lights', 'Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Disc Suspension Lights were designed by the founders and creative force behind the Graypants team, Jonathan Junker and Seth Grizzle. Handcrafted from recycled cardboard, Graypants\' flagship Scraplight series provides warm, intimate, and functional lighting for any occasion or type of space. Tough and elegant, each shade is precision cut with a laser and assembled by hand using a nontoxic adhesive. All Scraplights are treated with an environmentally friendly, no-burn fire retardant and are designed to perform flawlessly in both commercial applications and residential projects. The Discs are very engaging by themselves, in clusters of different dimensions , or presented with other Scraplight designs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: H 7.5\" X W 16.5<br />\r\nMeasurements: H 9\" X W 20\"<br />\r\nMeasurements: H 10.5\" W 24</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials:&nbsp;Handmade Shade, Natural, Cord and Powder Coated Canopy in Black,&nbsp;Blonde and White, Cord and Powder Coated Canopy in White,&nbsp;Bulbs: E26, 60W 120V Medium Base (Not Included)</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Architects Seth Grizzle and Jonathan Junker introduced their flagship line of pendant lights made entirely of repurposed corrugated cardboard in 2007. Their Scraplights quickly became a prime example of the principles that Graypants embodies to this day – responsible design, responsible materials, and responsible production. In 2012, their Amsterdam studio was founded to become a hub for local European production and distribution to over forty countries and has partnered with social works programs to provide craft-based work where needed the most. Today, Graypants continues to expand its custom portfolio, from architectural installations to public artworks, and has numerous product lines sold throughout the world. The range of their work is comprehensive, covering residential and commercial lighting, furniture, packaging designs, and architecture.</p>\r\n', '485', '780', 'en', 21),
