fort. His space-age creations remain immensely popular and reinforce the appeal and enduring relevance of 1960s design.</p>\r\n', '3965.00', '', 'en', 23),
(23, 'F 587 Chair', 'Geoffrey Harcourt', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Geoffrey Harcourt initially developed the 500 Series of chairs for Artifort in 1967. The F 587 L chair is the lower companion to the high-back F 587 chair. In 2011 Harcourt delivered a blueprint to Artifort for an updated, four star, polished stainless steel base as an alternative to the classic, round swivel base. The F 587s are configured exclusively with this four star base and have tufted, loose cushions for a luxurious, tactile presentation and classic, refined aesthetics. You will find that each 500 Series variation offers unsurpassed comfort and an equally evocative aesthetic experience. Note the F 510 and F 511 designs with their extra-thick cushion elements for a slightly more plush alternative to the tailored F 584 and F 585. Please call our expert, trained sales consultants with any questions you may have about designing a 500 Series chair and ottoman to match your specific, functional and aesthetic requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, F 587 Chair: W 36.2\" X H 37.4\" X D 36.2\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, F 587 L Chair, W 32.3\" X H 32.8\" X D 33.5\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Ottoman: W 24.4\" X H 15\" X D 19.7\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials, Tufted Loose Cushions with Buttons, Polished Four Star Stainless Steel Base, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Geoffrey Harcourt played a critical role in Artifort’s development and transition into the contract furniture market in the early 1960s. His distinctively styled, ergonomic desk chairs gave Artifort international recognition and helped fuel rapid growth and expansion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geoffrey Harcourt trained at the Royal Academy of Art in London and has earned numerous international design awards and honors. In 1978 he received the prestigious “Royal Designer for Industry” award by the RSA (Royal Society for the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce), a title introduced in 1936 to honor designers of excellence and promote important contributions of design in manufacturing and industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harcourt’s perhaps best known for his exceptional 500 Series of classic lounge chairs designed for Artifort. The chairs illustrate his talent for balancing clean aesthetics, superb ergonomics and comfort. His space-age creations remain immensely popular and reinforce the appeal and enduring relevance of 1960s design.</p>\r\n', '3735.00', '', 'en', 24),
(24, 'Gap Chair', 'Khodi Feiz ', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The versatile Gap chair was designed by Khodi Feiz in 2007. Its fluid balance and structural \"gap\" between the back and seat give the design a unique look suitable for numerous residential and commercial applications. The design can be specified with 4 leg, sledge or a 5 leg, height-adjustable office version with castors. Each shares the same ergonomic seat configuration and provides superb comfort. The Gap chair is available with chrome, polished aluminum or powder coat bases for enhanced personalization and easy adaptation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 4 Leg Base: W 24.4\" X H 33.5\" X D 23.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Sledge Base: W 25.2\" X H 33.5\" X D 23.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 5 Leg, Height Adjustable Base: W 25.2\" X H 31.1\" - 34.3\" X D 25.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Chrome, Polished Aluminum or Powder Coat Base Options, High-Density Cushion Core, Flex-Frame, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Khodi Feiz is an industrial designer who was born in Iran and grew up in the USA. A graduate of Syracuse University in New York, he moved to the Netherlands in 1990 to work together with graphic designer Anneko Feiz-van Dorsen, where they specialize in the fields of product design, furniture design, graphic design, and strategic design for companies such as Alessi, Artifort, Hernam Miller, Offecct, Nike and Nokia. Feiz\'s work has received numerous international design awards and has been featured in exhibitions and publications worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Khodi Feiz on Artifort: \"In a way, I like to see Artifort not as a company in the business of making furniture, but in the business of making history. I strongly believe in lasting relationships where designer and producer have time to understand each others\' potentiality. This is true now more than ever as progress is measured in fleeting instances as opposed to depth and quality. It is precisely this relationship Artifort has neutered throughout the decades starting with legends such as Pierre Paulin, Kho Liang Ie, and Geoffrey Harcourt, and still continuing today with talented contemporary designers like Patrick Norguet, Jasper Morrison, and Richard Hutten.\"</p>\r\n', '1322.00', '', 'en', 25),
(25, 'Gap Office Chair ', 'Khodi Feiz ', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The versatile Gap chair was designed by Khodi Feiz in 2007. Its fluid balance and structural \"gap\" between the back and seat give the design a pleasant, unique look suitable for numerous residential and commercial applications. The design can be specified with 4 leg, sledge or a 5 leg, height-adjustable office version with castors. Each shares the same ergonomic seat configuration and provides superb comfort. The Gap chair is available with chrome, polished aluminum or powder coat bases for enhanced personalization and easy adaptation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 4 Leg Base: W 24.4\" X H 33.5\" X D 23.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Sledge Base: W 25.2\" X H 33.5\" X D 23.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 5 Leg, Height Adjustable Base: W 25.2\" X H 31.1\" X 34,3\" X D 25.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Chrome, Polished Aluminum or Powder Coat Base Options, High-Density Cushion Core, Flex-Frame, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Khodi Feiz is an industrial designer who was born in Iran and grew up in the USA. A graduate of Syracuse University in New York, he moved to the Netherlands in 1990 to work together with graphic designer Anneko Feiz-van Dorsen, where they specialize in the fields of product design, furniture design, graphic design, and strategic design for companies such as Alessi, Artifort, Hernam Miller, Offecct, Nike and Nokia. Feiz\'s work has received numerous international design awards and has been featured in exhibitions and publications worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Khodi Feiz on Artifort: \"In a way, I like to see Artifort not as a company in the business of making furniture, but in the business of making history. I strongly believe in lasting relationships where designer and producer have time to understand each others\' potentiality. This is true now more than ever as progress is measured in fleeting instances as opposed to depth and quality. It is precisely this relationship Artifort has neutered throughout the decades starting with legends such as Pierre Paulin, Kho Liang Ie, and Geoffrey Harcourt, and still continuing today with talented contemporary designers like Patrick Norguet, Jasper Morrison, and Richard Hutten.\"</p>\r\n', '1494.00', '', 'en', 26),
(26, 'Gemini Seating', 'Ben van Berkel', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Ben van Berkel\'s 2014 Gemini is full of movement, dynamism and Artifort DNA. Gemini comprises two asymmetrically-designed seat elements and a matching table. The design offers options for mixing and matching different colored upholstery selections to create highly compelling, personally-tailored compositions. The choices and possibilities are nearly endless. Gemini\'s one-piece seat shell invites the user to sit upright, or lounge and relax in comfort. One side of its shell almost reaches to the ground, while the other side flows upwards to form an ergonomically balanced backrest and contoured armrest. Gemini is particularly well suited for reception areas, lounges, lobbies and other commercial project settings where high-style, beauty and long-term utilitarian performance are required. Please call our expert, trained sales consultants directly with any questions you may have about designing a Gemini seating configuration to match your specific aesthetic and functional requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 31.5\" X H 34.6 X D 32.3\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Asymmetrical Metal Frame in Powder Coat Finish, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>UN Studio practices architecture as a discipline that possesses a wide range of scales and dimensions. The house, the department store, the railway station, the museum, the temporary installation and the theoretical manifesto are all intricate parts of their oeuvre. In recent years, the sofa, the chair, and the table have become integral parts of their extended body of work. The same enquiring and experimental attitude in which UN Studio approaches architecture is also employed in their designing of products.&nbsp; Designing furniture in the classical tradition of the architect/designer means the UN Studio\'s designs are related to architecture functionality. UN Studio\'s approach to product designs is based on the combination of a deep understanding and working knowledge of materials and innovative technology with distinctive spatial design strategies.</p>\r\n', '2575.00', '', 'en', 27),
(27, 'Hanna Chair', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten\'s 2001 Hanna design for Artifort is a compact, comfortable lounge chair suitable for both high-style residential settings and the most demanding commercial applications. The Hanna\'s stout, three leg support system creates a dynamic counterpoint to its fluidly contoured seat shell. The overall, top-to-bottom balance is extremely appealing and allows the Hanna to be easily positioned in multiple variations and grouped configurations to foster relaxed interaction and conversation. Holten\'s design is now available in a wide variety of durable powder coat leg finishes as well as the standard, polished chrome finish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 27.6\" X H 28.3\" X D 32.3\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Steel Legs, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '2909.00', '', 'en', 28),
(28, 'Libel Chair', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten\'s inventive Libel (2000) can be used as a stand-alone chair or linked to enable inward or outward curved rows. The design is exceptionally strong and constructed for demanding, high-traffic project applications. Functional tablets and armrests can be applied to individual seating units or joined together to create interlocking assemblages. Legs are available in polished chrome or durable powder coat finishes. Please contact our sales staff directly with any questions you may have about configuring a Libel design to meet your specific requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Armless Chair: W 29.9\" X H 28.7\" X D 27.1\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Table or Upholstered Arm Chair: W 35.8 X H 28.7\" X D 27.1\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Metal Frame and Legs in Polished Chrome or Powder Coat Finish, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '1991.00', '', 'en', 29),
(29, 'Lilla Stool', 'Patrick Norguet', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Patrick Norguet designed the Lilla stool for Artifort in 2006. It\'s organic form resembles the natural character of a tree-trunk. The design is deceptively simple and inviting. Norguet\'s creation distinguishes itself in both color and material selection and works exceptionally well in small to medium-sized groups in lobbies, convention halls and other commercial hospitality settings. The affect of a series of brightly colored Lilla stools arrayed together creates a powerful visual statement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 14.2\" X H 21.7\" X D 15\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Contoured Frame Structure, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Patrick Norguet (1969) made his breakthrough as a designer at the end of the 1990s. In 2002, he designed the successful Apollo lounge chair for Artifort. Since then, Norguet has gone on to design the Little Apollo chair, Boson chair, Lex series, and Manhattan modular seating among others for Artifort. Norguet is also celebrated for designing the interior of the Renault showroom and the Lancel shop on the Champs-Elysees in Paris. Prestigious museums around the world have included products designed by Norguet in their permanent collections.</p>\r\n', '691.00', '', 'en', 30),
(30, 'Little Apollo Bar Stool', 'Patrick Norguet', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Little Apollo stools were developed in 2004 based on Patrick Norguet\'s original Apollo lounge chair conceived in 2002. The Little Apollo bar and counter-height designs share the larger Apollo\'s beautifully contoured shape in precisely scaled down, creatively repurposed variations. They\'re perfect as stylish residential stools but also works well in commercial applications in restaurants, cafes, reception areas, and design-driven offices. The Little Apollo bases are finished in durable, polished chrome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Counter Height: W 26.8\" X H 39\" D 24\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Bar Height: W 26.8\" X H 47.2\" X D 24\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Tubular Steel Frame with Polished Chrome Finish, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Patrick Norguet (1969) made his breakthrough as a designer at the end of the 1990s. In 2002, he designed the successful Apollo lounge chair for Artifort. Since then, Norguet has gone on to design the Little Apollo chair, Boson chair, Lex series, and Manhattan modular seating among others for Artifort. Norguet is also celebrated for designing the interior of the Renault showroom and the Lancel shop on the Champs-Elysees in Paris. Prestigious museums around the world have included products designed by Norguet in their permanent collections.</p>\r\n', '1560', '', 'en', 31);
