(31, 'Little Apollo Chair', 'Patrick Norguet', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Little Apollo is the smaller, side chair version of Patrick Norguet\'s exceptionally designed Apollo lounge chair conceived in 2002. The Little Apollo was developed in 2004 and reflects the larger Apollo\'s beautifully contoured shape in a scaled down size. It\'s perfect as a stylish dining room chair but also works well in commercial applications in restaurants, cafes, reception areas, and offices. The Little Apollo can be specified with the classic swivel trumpet base as well as a 4 leg version and a stylish sledge base. A wide assortment of powder coat finish options are now available in addition to the classic, original polished aluminum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 4 Leg Base: W 26.8\" X H 33.1\" X D 24.2\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Sledge Base: W 26.8\" X H 33.1\" X D 24.2\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Swivel Base: W 26.8\" X H 33.1\" X D 24.2\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Metal Framework, High-Density Cushion Core, Polished Aluminum or Powder Coat Finishes, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Patrick Norguet (1969) made his breakthrough as a designer at the end of the 1990s. In 2002, he designed the successful Apollo lounge chair for Artifort. Since then, Norguet has gone on to design the Little Apollo chair, Boson chair, Lex series, and Manhattan modular seating among others for Artifort. Norguet is also celebrated for designing the interior of the Renault showroom and the Lancel shop on the Champs-Elysees in Paris. Prestigious museums around the world have included products designed by Norguet in their permanent collections.</p>\r\n', '1208.00', '', 'en', 32),
(32, 'Little Tulip Stool', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Little Tulip stool was adapted from Pierre Paulin\'s popular Little Tulip chair of 1965. The Little Tulip chair is a design icon and one of the most coveted Paulin works produced by Artifort. The bar stool designs share the same appealing contours and comfort of the Little Tulip chairs and can be specified in both standard bar-height or counter-height variations. The stools\' compact dimensions and clearly recognizable, iconic style make them the perfect choice for a wide array of residential and commercial applications. The classic, polished aluminum swivel base adds to the designs\' visual presence and functionality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurement, Counter-Height: W 26\" X H 35.4\" X D 22.9\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Bar-Height: W 26\" X H 43.3\" X D 22.9\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Beech Wood Seat Shell, High-Density Cushion Core, Polished Aluminum Disk Base, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '1521.00', '', 'en', 33),
(34, 'Mare Chair', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Mare chair is available in two size configurations and works well in both modern and traditional surroundings. René Holten\'s popular 2003 design has a tightly upholstered back and slim, polished chrome legs that seamlessly flow into the frame structure. The Mare line is available in many variations with both thin and wide arms, including: 2 seat, 2.2 seat, 2.5 seat and 3 seat sofas. The Mare Romance sofa (2006) with loose back cushions and More Mare modular sectional design (2008) both build on and expand Holten\'s original design and reinforce its fundamental aesthetic and functional purity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Small Chair: W 34.3\" X H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Large Chair: W 45.3\" H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Ottoman: W 32.7</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Materials: Polished Stainless Steel or Powder Coat Frame, High Density Foam Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '2938.00', '', 'en', 35),
(35, 'Mare Ottoman', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Mare ottoman was designed by René Holten in 2003 as a companion item to the Mare sofas. Holten\'s design is elegant, timeless and suits both modern and transitional interiors. The Mare Romance sofa (2006) with loose back cushions and More Mare modular sectional (2008) both build on and expand Holten\'s original Mare designs and reinforce their fundamental aesthetic and functional purity. The original ottoman works seamlessly with each design in the Mare family of products and can now be enhanced with a wide assortment of Artifort powder coat frame colors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: Width 32.7\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Polished Stainless Steel or Powder Coat Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '1844', '', 'en', 36),
(36, 'Mare Loose Cushion Seating', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Mare Loose Cushion&nbsp;is a sleek, timeless sofa that suits both modern and traditional surroundings. René Holten\'s 2006 design has two loose back cushions and slim, polished stainless steel legs that seamlessly flow into the frame structure. Mare&nbsp;is available in many variants, including: 2 seat, 2.5 seat and 3 seat sofas and a lounge chair and ottoman as well as modular units.&nbsp;The original Mare sofa (2003) with its tight back and crisply defined center accent-line offers a slightly firmer alternative&nbsp;to the Mare Loose Cushion&nbsp;and is an equally popular choice.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 2 Seat: W 58.7\" X H 28.3\" X D 33.5\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 2.5 Seat: W 80.3\" X H 28.3\" X D 33.5\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 3 Seat: W 92.5\" X H 28.3\" X D 33.5\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Polished Stainless Steel Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery, Optional Tufted Upholstery with Oiled Oak Buttons</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '4287', '', 'en', 37),
(37, 'Mare Fixed Cushion Seating', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Mare is a sleek, timeless sofa that suits both modern and transitional interiors. René Holten\'s popular 2003 design has tightly upholstered cushions and slim, polished stainless steel legs that seamlessly flow into the frame structure. A distinctive, signature groove in the middle of the sofa elegantly divides the comfortable two seating sections and enhances the visual sophistication of the design. The Mare sofa is available with both thin and wide arms and can be specified in 2 seat, 2.2 seat, 2.5 seat, and 3 seat configurations. The Mare Loose Cushion sofa (2006) and expansive Mare modular designs (2008) build on and expand Holten\'s original design and reinforce its fundamental aesthetic and functional purity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 2 Seat: W 58.7\" X H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 2.2 Seat: W 68.9\" X H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 2.5 Seat: W 80.3\" X H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 3 Seat: W 92.5\" X H 29.1\" X D 32.7\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Polished Stainless Steel Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '4116', '', 'en', 38),
(38, 'Megan Chair', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten created the Megan chair for Artifort in 2005 as a multipurpose design suitable for a wide range of commercial and residential settings. The gracefully curved seat shell provides excellent support and works well as a dining chair, office reception chair or utilitarian boardroom design. Megan can be specified with the following leg and base support structures in both standard and low variations: 4 Leg, 4 Leg Low, Sledge, Sledge Low, 4 Star Non-Swiveling, 4 Star Swiveling and a 5 Star, height adjustable office design. Additional aesthetic options include the choice of polished chrome or Artifort\'s durable, powder coat color finishes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 4 Leg: W 24\" X H 32.3\" D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Leg Low: W 24\" H 29.9\" X D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Sledge: W 24\" X H 33.5\" X D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Sledge, Low: W 24\" H 29.9\" X D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Star: W 24\" X H 33.5\" X D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Star, Swivel with Return: W 24\" H 33.5\" X D 25.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 5 Star with Castors: W 24\" X H 31.1-34.3\" X D 25.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Seat Shell, Base in Polished Chrome or Powder Coat Finish, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '1299.00', '', 'en', 39),
(39, 'Mood Chair', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten\'s 2014 Mood chair is an elegantly refined design with multiple base and upholstery options. Leg and base selections have a particularly powerful impact on the chair\'s dynamics, visual character and overall aesthetic balance. The design is available with wire, four-leg wood, four-leg stainless, disk and rolling-castor bases to suit nearly any project. Bases can be specified in a wide assortment of materials, including wood and Artifort powder coat colors. The comfortable bucket seat is available in two tone fabric as well as elegant cross-stitching for an added accent for leather upholstery. Please contact or expert, trained sales staff with any questions you may have about selecting the perfect Mood chair for your specific aesthetic and functional requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 22.4\" X H 31.1\" X D 24.8\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Office Chair: W 25.2\" X H 28.3\"-32.3\" X D 25.2\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Bases in Wire, Four-Leg Wood, Four-Leg Stainless, Disk (Swiveling and Non-Swiveling), Powder Coat Finishes, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '1319.00', '', 'en', 40),
(40, 'Mare Modular ', 'René Holten', '<p>More Mare is the logical extension of René Hoten\'s stylish Mare sofa. The design is a combination of separate components from the Mare collection with new elements, such as a 90 degree angle, 135 degree angle, and chaise lounge. Rene Holten\'s popular, 2008 design has tightly upholstered cushions and slim, polished aluminum legs that seamlessly flow into the frame structure. A distinctive, signature groove in the middle of the main seating sections elegantly divides and enhances the visual sophistication of the design. The Mare collection also includes the original Mare sofa (2003) and the Mare loose cushion back variation (2006).&nbsp;Please contact our expert, trained sales consultants with any questions you may have about designing a Mare to match your specific aesthetic and functional requirements.</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '8169.00', '', 'en', 41),
(42, 'Moulin Chair', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The design of the Moulin Chair dates from Pierre Paulin\'s early years and was developed on the Rue Jean Moulin. Formally in the collection of Thonet France, the 1954 design now resides in Artifort\'s permanent collection of iconic Paulin works. The simple, modest design with its slim metal frame and crisply upholstered elements works exceptionally well as a refined breakfast or occasional chair. The Moulin\'s clearly delineated, resolute structural form and practical nature predates the experimentation of Paulin\'s later, sculptural work of the 1960s and 1970s and represents a reference point in the evolution of his design career. It\'s the perfect Artifort addition for the Paulin aficionado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Armless Chair: W 18.9\" X H 34.3\" X D 20.9\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Arm Chair: W 23.2 X H 34.3\" X D 20.9\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Metal Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Powder Coat Finishes</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '922.00', '', 'en', 43),
(43, 'Mushroom Chair', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Mushroom chair is a Pierre Paulin classic and rests in the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York. Bold, bulbous and organic, the Mushroom chair has been providing great comfort and eliciting ebullient responses for over 50 years. In 2013 Artifort added a diminutive Mushroom Junior chair based on Paulin\'s designs and re-introduced the slightly more expansive, classic Big Mushroom chair. Now there\'s a perfect seating solution for everyone who appreciates timeless design and comfort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Chair: W 35.4\" X H 26.4<br />\r\nMeasurements, Ottoman: W 18.1\" X H 15\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Metal Framework, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric or Leather</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '2804', '', 'en', 44),
