(47, 'Nina with Castors ', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten\'s Nina chair has been a staple of the Artifort collection since its design and debut in 2000. Its sculptural form and elegant composition fits perfectly within the Artifort design tradition. The Nina\'s rounded, fitted back provides comfortable support, making it an ideal choice for well-appointed dining room and conference room applications. The design strikes the perfect balance of aesthetics, functionality, and long-term durability. Holten\'s design is available in 4 variations: a polished chrome 4 leg base, a 4 star polished aluminum base in both non-swiveling and swiveling versions, and a 5 leg, height adjustable office chair in polished aluminum. Each design can also be specified with Artifort\'s vibrant powder coat color finishes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, 4 Leg Base: W 24.4\" X H 31.1\" X D 24.4\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Star Base, Non-Swiveling: W 24.4\" X H 31.1\" X D 24.4\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Star Base, Swiveling with Return: W 24.4\" X H 31.1\" X D 24.4\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 5 Star Base, Height Adjustable: W 24.4\" X H 31.1\" - 34.3\" X D 25.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Polished Chrome, Polished Aluminum or Powder Coat Base Finishes, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '1202.00', '', 'en', 48),
