>\r\n', '1031.00', '', 'en', 49),
(49, 'Ondo Sofa', 'René Holten', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">René Holten designed the Ondo Sofa in 2003. The sofa\'s clean, polished chrome support structure and elegantly flowing lines set the design apart from the competition. Its integrated back and seating area seamlessly merge, creating a relaxed and comfortable position. The design has an inviting, airy, and weightless aesthetic quality that belies its solidity and robust structural strength. The Ondo is built to last and is the perfect choice for high-traffic commercial applications in lobbies, hotels, and design-driven reception areas. An Ondo can also provide the perfect anchor for many of Pierre Paulin\'s highly sculptural lounge chair designs. The juxtaposition of these enticing shapes can have a transformative effect on contemporary environments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 88.6\" X H 27.5\" X D 30\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Polished Chrome or Powder Coated Steel Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '5841.00', '', 'en', 50),
(50, 'Orange Slice Chair', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Orange Slice chair was originally conceived by Pierre Paulin in 1960 and remains one of his most influential and highly regarded designs. The chair\'s unique structure employs two perfectly identical shells of pressed beech wood wrapped in high-density cushion core. Pierre Paulin\'s iconic design has a strong and resolute stance, looks great from any angle and sets the standard for overall comfort and ease of use. The Orange Slice works beautifully in contemporary residential settings as well as the most demanding commercial applications. In 2013 Artifort added a diminutive Orange Slice Junior chair based on Paulin\'s designs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 31.5\" x H 27.6\" x D 33\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Two Pressed Beech Wood Shells, High-Density Cushion Core, Polished Chrome Frame and Base</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '2761', '', 'en', 51),
(51, 'Orange Slice Junior Chair', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">If you’re a design lover and your son or daughter likes to have their own chair with the “big people” than Artifort’s Junior Collection is for you. There are now diminutive versions of the classic Orange Slice and Mushroom chairs. Both are identical to the original model but scaled down to junior size. They are also developed by Artifort and methodically crafted by the same people that make the original models. The designs make inspiring gifts and are exceptionally built pieces of furniture that are sure to be happily passed down to future generations of design enthusiasts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 24.4” X H 21.3” X D 24.4”</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Two Pressed Beech Wood Shells, High-Density Cushion Core, Polished Chrome Frame and Legs</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '912.00', '', 'en', 52),
(52, 'Orange Slice Table', 'Pierre Paulin', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Orange Slice coffee table designs have a dynamic leg structure that aligns with Pierre Paulin\'s iconic (1960) Orange Slice chair and ottoman. Their simple, clean lines work well with a wide assortment of classic Paulin lounge chairs and contemporary Artifort designs. Orange Slice coffee tables are available in two sizes and can be specified with durable laminates or an oak veneer top. Each variation offers exceptional durability for residential and commercial interiors. Orange Slice table legs are now available in vibrant Artifort powder coat colors as well as the classic polished chrome finish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Table 1: W 27.6\" X H 13.8\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, Table 2: W 39.4\" X H 15.7\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: White or Black Laminate, or Oak Veneer Tops with Black Milled Edge, Legs in Powder Coat or Polished Chrome Finish</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Mention Artifort and Pierre Paulin immediately springs to mind. The brand and designer are inextricably linked. Their deep bond and collaborative history are legendary within the design world and each, undeniably, drove the other to greater heights of commercial success and critical acclaim. By the early 1960s Paulin\'s sculptural designs were so successful and sought after in the international market that Artifort\'s production facilities could barely keep up with demand. French presidents Pompidou and Mitterand commissioned Paulin to design interiors in the Elysee Palace in Paris, further amplifying his notoriety and significance as a visionary, multi-talented designer. Pierre Paulin continued to design and collaborate with Artifort until his death on June 13th, 2009 in Montpellier, France. In November, 2009 Paulin was posthumously awarded the prestigious title, \"Royal Designer of Industry\" by the Royal Society of the Encouragement of Arts, Manufacturers and Commerce. Today, Pierre Paulin designs are included in permanent collections of prestigious museums throughout the world.</p>\r\n', '1112.00', '', 'en', 53),
(54, 'Paco Chair', 'Gerard Vollenbrock', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">Gerard Vollenbrock\'s 2009 Paco chair is comfortable, functional and highly versatile. It can be specified as a simple 4 leg chair, 4 leg task chair with soft castors, 5 leg, height-adjustable office chair or elegant sledge base design for dining room applications. Each variation is clearly identified by its crisply formed, angled arm supports, and taught seat and back sections. Light, strong and stylish, Paco is perfect for myriad residential and commercial applications. The design can also be special ordered with a contrasting leather or fabric accent color on the inside back of the armrest. Please call for details and pricing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Sledge Chair: W 23.2\" X H 33.1\" D 23.2\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Leg Chair: W 23.2\" X H 33.1\" X D 23.6\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 4 Leg with Soft Castors: W 23.2\" X H 33.1\" X D 23.2\"<br />\r\nMeasurements, 5 Leg Height Adjustable Chair: W 24\" X H 31.9\" - 35\" X 25.6\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Bases in Chrome, Polished Aluminum or Powder Coat Finish, Flex-Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Gerard Vollenbrock (1949) lives and works in Arnhem and on the Greek island Serifos. He studied graphic design at the Academy of Art and Industry in Enschede and fine art at Academy of Art in Arnhem. Vollenbrock has been working as a furniture designer since 1984 but also taught furniture and interior design between 1987 and 1992 at the Minerva Academy in Groningen. His designs have been included in the collections of Artifort, Geldeland, Castelijn, Leolux, Lande and Linteloo, among others. Vollenbrock\'s designs are largely determined by his mastery of the use of form, space and materials and fit perfectly within the tradition of contemporary Dutch design. In 2009 he created the elegantly versatile and subtly detailed Paco chair for Arifort.</p>\r\n', '1212.00', '', 'en', 55),
