(86, 'F 51-3 Sofa', 'Walter Gropius', '<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">The Walter Gropius designed cubist F 51 armchair and sofa suite combine voluminous upholstery with a novel frame. This intersection of volume and linearity is reminiscent of contemporary architecture projects by Gropius, particularly the residential building that he referred to as Baukasten im Grossen (Large-scale building kit). But the frame of this armchair is significant for another reason. The armrests protrude freely and even the back of the chair does not touch the ground. When the upholstery is removed, this cantilever armrest structure reveals itself as a precursor of the cantilever chairs, and anticipates, if turned 90 degrees, Marcel Breuer’s stool on runners from 1925. Walter Gropius\' timeless and comfortable F 51-3 sofa is a masterwork of functional design and works beautifully in discerning residential or high-traffic commercial settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 84.6\" X H 27.6\" X D 29.5\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Materials: Solid Ash, Solid Oak or Solid Walnut, Selected Lacquer color, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '<p>Walter Gropius established his own architecture and industrial design practice in 1910. His output in this period included wallpapers, mass-produced interior furnishings, car bodies and even a diesel locomotive. The Fagus Factory in Alfeld an der Leine, which he designed together with Adolf Meyer, would be his first major architectural work. With its transparent façade of steel and glass, this factory building is widely held to be a pioneering work of what later became known as Modern Architecture, evolving eventually in the 1920s into the Neues Bauen - New Objectivity movement. The Fagus Factory was awarded UNESCO World Heritage status in June 2011. After the First World War, Gropius became a founding member of the Bauhaus. In 1919 he succeeded Henry van de Veldes as the Director of the Großherzoglich-Sächsischen Hochschule für Bildende Kunst in Weimar and renamed the institute Staatliches Bauhaus in Weimar. Gropius held the office of Director in Weimar until 1926 and subsequently in Dessau. He was succeeded by Ludwig Mies van der Rohe, who directed the Bauhaus until its closure in 1933. Gropius immigrated to England in 1934, following a smear campaign by the Nazis, who branded the Bauhaus a Church of Marxism. In 1937 he relocated to Cambridge, Massachusetts, where he served as a professor of architecture at Harvard University’s Graduate School of Design.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '8114', '', 'en', 87),
(89, 'Manhattan Modular', 'René Holten', '', 'basic_description', '<p>René Holten (1961) is a graduate of the Design Academy in Eindhoven. Holten has been designing award winning products for Artifort since 1997, including: Nina, Ondo, Lotus, Low Lotus, Hana, Ping, and&nbsp;the complete, expanded, Mare Collection. His designs have enjoyed critical acclaim as well as broad commercial success in the high-end commercial and residential furniture markets. René Holten\'s designs for Artifort are continually fluid, comfortable and appealing. Whether round and sculptural&nbsp;or crisp, clean and linear, Holten\'s designs appeal to the senses and are works of high aesthetic and&nbsp;functional value.</p>\r\n', '3000', '', 'en', 90),
(90, 'Mushroom Chair', '', '<p>The Mushroom chair is a Pierre Paulin classic and rests in the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York. Bold, bulbous and organic, the Mushroom chair has been providing great comfort and eliciting ebullient responses for over 50 years. In 2013 Artifort added a diminutive Mushroom Junior chair based on Paulin\'s designs and re-introduced the slightly more expansive, classic Big Mushroom chair. Now there\'s a perfect seating solution for everyone who appreciates timeless design and comfort.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Measurements, Chair: W 35.4\" X H 26.4</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>Measurements, Ottoman: W 18.1\" X H 15\"</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Metal Framework, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric or Leather</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '', '', 'en', 91),
(91, 'Mushroom Chair Demo ', '', '<p>The Mushroom chair is a Pierre Paulin classic and rests in the permanent collection of the Museum of Modern Art in New York. Bold, bulbous and organic, the Mushroom chair has been providing great comfort and eliciting ebullient responses for over 50 years. In 2013 Artifort added a diminutive Mushroom Junior chair based on Paulin\'s designs and re-introduced the slightly more expansive, classic Big Mushroom chair. Now there\'s a perfect seating solution for everyone who appreciates timeless design and comfort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements, Chair: W 35.4\" X H 26.4<br />\r\nMeasurements, Ottoman: W 18.1\" X H 15\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Metal Framework, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric or Leather</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '', '', 'en', 92),
(92, 'Orange Slice Chair Demo', '', '<p>The Orange Slice chair was originally conceived by Pierre Paulin in 1960 and remains one of his most influential and highly regarded designs. The chair\'s unique structure employs two perfectly identical shells of pressed beech wood wrapped in high-density cushion core. Pierre Paulin\'s iconic design has a strong and resolute stance, looks great from any angle and sets the standard for overall comfort and ease of use. The Orange Slice works beautifully in contemporary residential settings as well as the most demanding commercial applications. In 2013 Artifort added a diminutive Orange Slice Junior chair based on Paulin\'s designs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 31.5\" x H 27.6\" x D 33\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Two Pressed Beech Wood Shells, High-Density Cushion Core, Polished Chrome Frame and Base</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '', '', 'en', 93),
(94, 'Jima Chairs ', '', '<p>Form, function, comfort and exceptional detail: the Jima chair by Patrick Norguet checks all the boxes. This sleek, expressive chair will fit seamlessly into different many worlds - elegant office or refined residential. Particularly noteworthy is the single, flowing line running from the top of the back, via the arms to the bottom of the seat. This makes it appear as if the seat cushion is locked in an embrace, providing flexibility and maximum comfort. Jima comes in high back and low back versions, and is available in four different bases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 23.3\" X H 31.4\" D 24\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: High Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric or Leather, choice of Bases in Polished Aluminum or Ash Wood&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact us for complete details on Jima chair options and price variations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '1126', '', 'en', 95),
(95, 'Chaise Lounge ', '', '<p>Countless designers have been inspired by the idea behind the traditional chaise longue. Geoffrey Harcourt\'s interpretation from 1970 shattered all previous conceptions of the form and catapulted it into the modern realm. Acknowledged as a masterwork on a par with Pierre Paulin\'s greatest works, the Harcourt chaise lounge remains a functional icon of modern design. Integrated castors add to its appeal and usability in both commercial and high-end residential settings.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 75.6\" X H 26\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Tubular Steel Frame, High-Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric, Integrated Castors with Locking Capability</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '5999', '', 'en', 96),
(101, 'Shark Chair ', '', '<p>Artifort presented the Shark chair at Salone del Mobile in 2011 to great critical acclaim. The chair acquired its fierce name because its profile resembled that of the feared predator, but you have nothing to fear from this shark. On the contrary, it’s an extremely friendly, comfortable chair to sit in and relax. The Shark is a top Artifort seller and works equally well in dining room and conference room settings. The design’s appeal and versatility is further enhanced by its various base options, including four-legged, swiveling, and sledge configurations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 23.6\" X H 33\" X D 25.6\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Steel Frame, Molded wood Seat, High-Density Cushion Core, Four-Legged, Sledge, or Swivel Base in Powder Coat or Polished Aluminum&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '1068', '', 'en', 102),
(102, 'Suit Chair', '', '<p>There’s nothing better than making a good first impression that combines professional elegance with an individual personality. With the fully upholstered Suit chair, Monica Förster introduces a new standard of seating comfort for restaurants, workplaces and homeowners with a strong sense of style. The distinctive silhouette of the Suit, with its elegant open back and flowing lines, effortlessly matches the contours of the body. It’s a surprisingly comfortable and inviting design, whose soft upholstery embraces the user like a chic tailor-made suit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 23.2” X H 32.7” X D 22.4”&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Metal Frame, Molded Foam, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '1537', '', 'en', 103),
(103, 'Pala Chair ', '', '<p>Pala is a fully upholstered armchair on a pedestal conceived&nbsp;by Italian designer Luca Nichetto. It’s Nichetto’s first design for Artifort and is an exquisite aesthetic and ergonomic accomplishment in terms of sheer beauty and&nbsp;utilitarian comfort. The design follows the shape of a human body and combines Artifort’s heritage with a contemporary Italian sensibility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 29.9” X H 38.1” X D 33.8”&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Heavy Gauge Steel Wire Framework, Molded Foam, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '3388', '', 'en', 104),
(104, 'Kalm Lounge Seating ', '', '<p>Kalm is Artifort’s large, cozy armchair by French designer Patrick Norguet. It\'s&nbsp;a sanctuary in its own right, a place to unwind and get comfortable. With Kalm, Patrick Norguet has created a luxurious and comfortable high-back armchair for the &nbsp;living room or study. The&nbsp;design also works equally well in commercial settings. According to Norguet, it’s “an expressive armchair that is suitable in any project environment. Several Kalm armchairs grouped together will definitely define a hotel lobby or meeting room and create a distinguished and iconic image.\"&nbsp;Kalm (and the slightly more padded) Kalm Comfort can be combined with a matching ottoman, which has an upholstered cushion in the same shape as the cushion in the chair.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 36.2” X H 42.1” X D 32.3\"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Structural Steel, High-Density Cushion Core, 4 Legged Oiled Wood Base, Swivel Base With Selected Powder Coat,&nbsp;Or Polished Stainless Steel Finish</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '2925', '', 'en', 105),
(105, 'Apps Lounge Seating ', '', '<p>Apps is a cube with rounded corners, like an icon on a smart phone screen. Designed by Richard Hutten in accordance with the best Artifort traditions – it’s smooth, timeless and comfortable. Apps is available in an armchair and 2-seater sofa.&nbsp;The comfort of the Apps armchair or Apps sofa is excellent due to the use of stretch webbing in the back and an ingenious seating structure.The Apps series can be specified with two toned materials in both leather and fabric. Please contact us for specific options and suggested color compositions. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: Chair W 35.4” X H 30.3” X D 29.9”, Sofa W 56.7” X 30.3” X D 39.9”&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Hard Wood, High Density Cushion Core, Structural Webbing, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '3330', '', 'en', 106),
(106, 'Figura Modular Seating ', '', '<p>Soft and fluid lines are the foundation of Figura. Designer Khodi Feiz created&nbsp;flexible elements that seamlessly combine with each other to form&nbsp;endless configurations. Whether a simple sofa or an assemblage of individual components, Figura\'s soft, contoured lines will add a distinctive charm&nbsp;to any&nbsp;stylish interior. Figura allows for extensive possibilities for personalization, including: chaise longue options, high arms or low arms, choice of attached shelves, added upholstery piping, and even two seating heights. Cast aluminum legs are also available in a wide variety of attractive color coat options. Please contact us for a personal consultation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: Three Seat Version W 91.3” X H 31”X D 32.3” (Contact for All Sizing Options)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: High Density Cushion Core, Powder Coated Leg Structure, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '4822', '', 'en', 107),
(107, 'C 416 Sofa ', '', '<p>Kho Liang Ie’s iconic C 416 sofa was introduced by Artifort in 1960 and reflects the designer\'s&nbsp;voyage of discovery undertaken within the strict social constraints of the late 1950s. Ie’s intent was to create a dynamic contrast between soft materials and rigid structures. This resulted in a&nbsp;sofa that looks remarkable from any angle. The minimalist frame of the C 416 sofa and F 416 chair consists of a careful balance between brushed stainless steel and black coated metal elements, finished with slats made from Santos Pallisander (sustainable rosewood).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: Three Seat W 74.4” X H 28.7” X D 30.7”<br />\r\nMeasurements: Four Seat W 97.6” 28.7” X D 30.7”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Base Brushed Stainless Steel Or Powder Coat, Santos Pallisander Or Black Powder Coat Slats, High Density Cushion Core, Tufted Fabric or Leather&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '7414', '', 'en', 108),
(108, 'F 416 Chair ', '', '<p>Kho Liang Ie’s iconic F 416 chair was introduced by Artifort in 1960 and reflects the designer\'s voyage of discovery undertaken within the strict social constraints of the late 1950s. Ie’s intent was to create a dynamic contrast between soft materials and rigid structures. This resulted in a chair and sofa design that looks remarkable from any angle. The minimalist frame of the F 416 chair consists of a careful balance between brushed stainless steel and black coated metal elements, finished with slats made from Santos Pallisander (sustainable rosewood).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 27.9” X H 28.7 X D 30.7”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Base Brushed Stainless Steel Or Powder Coat, Santos Pallisander Or Black Powder Coat Slats, High Density Cushion Core, Selected Fabric or Leather</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '4247', '', 'en', 109),
(109, 'Big Island Sofas', '', '<p>Everyone has had the experience of living without a sofa for some period of time. To most of us this experience meant our homes were lacking the proper possibilities for retreating, deep relaxation and rejuvenation. This feeling inspired Norwegian designers Anderssen &amp; Voll to come up with a new modular sofa program for Artifort called Big Island. Their Big Island is&nbsp;a place to sit down, to settle your thoughts and to truly relax in your own home. The Big Island system is available in&nbsp;two standard sofa sizes with the addition of both left and right facing chaise units. Two color selections within the same fabric type are also possible to further amplify the appeal of the welcoming Big Island design. Please contact us for a personal consultation and details on color matching.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: 2.5 Seat W 86.6” X H 34.2” X D 33.5\"<br />\r\nMeasurements: 3 Seat W 98.4” H 34.2” X D 33.5”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Steel Frame, Multi Layered Dacron Foam with Duvet Top, Selected Fabrics, Two Color Variations Optional</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '5427', '', 'en', 110),
(110, 'Figura Arm Chair ', '', '<p>Soft and fluid lines are the foundation of Figura. Designer Khodi Feiz created flexible elements that seamlessly combine with each other to form endless configurations. Whether a simple sofa or an assemblage of individual components, Figura\'s soft, contoured lines will add a distinctive charm to any stylish interior. The Figura arm chair is the perfect, stout companion to Khodi Feiz’s modular sofa collection. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 40” X H 31” X D&nbsp;32.2”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: High Density Cushion Core, Powder Coated Leg Structure, Selected Upholster</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '3539', '', 'en', 111),
(112, 'Glider Chair ', '', '<p>Glider offers an attractive, relaxed seating experience in lobbies, lounges and residential settings. The gentle curvature of the upholstery and refined details make Luca Nichetto’s design stand out. Its elegant stitching and&nbsp;choice of rich fabrics and leathers lend allure and integrity to the design.&nbsp;The two shell sections provide exactly the right support for your&nbsp;back and shoulders and harmonizes with the natural shape of the body. Glider’s refined details can be admired from any angle, even from the back, making this armchair a perfect fit for open spaces. Two color fabrics or leathers and decorative stitching are available. Please contat us for a consultation and pricing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 35.4” X H 16.9” X D 31.1”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: Steel Frame In Powder Coat or Polished Chrome, Wood Seat Sheels, High Density Cushion Core, Seleted Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '2940', '', 'en', 113),
(113, 'Bras High Back Chair ', '', '<p>Khodi Feiz&nbsp;designed the Bras High Back chair for Artifort in 2016 as a companion piece to his popular Bras sofa collection. The chair invites you to relax, unwind and drift away. The ergonomically advanced design&nbsp;places a strong emphasis on the human form and clearly challenges more conventional design parameters. This is evidenced in the construction of the Bras armrest sections and how they conform to the natural arc of the arm when seated. The Bras design acknowledges that the arm does not bend at a perfect right angle; it bends at different joints in an angular curve. The exceptional structural composition of the armrests translates into greater comfort and increased support for the user. Bras High Back is available in a polished aluminum or powder coat swivel base and a four legged version in oiled ash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Measurements: W 35.4” X H 38.6” D 31.1”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Materials: High-Density Cushion Core, Swivel Base In Powder Coat, Polished Stainless Steel, Or Four Legged Ash Wood, Selected Upholstery</p>\r\n', 'basic_description', '', '3242', '', 'en', 114),
